FBIS4-12978 "drnes073_h_94001" FBIS-NES-94-073 Daily Report 14 Apr 1994 Tunisia Ben Ali Receives Message From Yemeni President Ben Ali Receives Message From Yemeni President LD1404203694 Tunis Tunis-7 Television in Arabic 1900 GMT 14 Apr 94 LD1404203694 Tunis Tunis-7 Television Arabic BFN [Excerpts] President Zine El Abidine Ben Ali received from Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih a letter, which was handed to him at Carthage Palace this morning by Yahya Husayn al-'Arashi, [Yemeni] minister [of civil service and administrative reform] and the Yemeni president's personal envoy to the president. [passage omitted] Yahya al-'Arashi made the following statement after the meeting: [Begin al-'Arashi recording] I was honored to meet his excellency President Zine El Abidine. I delivered a letter from his brother General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman of the Presidential Council of the Republic of Yemen. This was an appropriate occasion to inform the president of developments in Yemen, which is going through a passing crisis, God willing, and the national efforts being currently made at the level of dialogues in order to emerge from the crisis. We appreciate every effort, including Maghreban efforts that were demonstrated in the Tunis conference and the efforts made by President Zine El Abidine to support the Yemeni cause. [passage omitted] [end recording]
